470
00:55:28,600 --> 00:55:30,800
Come on in, Mr Fortlow.

471
00:55:36,800 --> 00:55:39,900
Corina, take the children
in the other room, please.

472
00:55:41,900 --> 00:55:43,900
Go on.

473
00:55:46,700 --> 00:55:50,500
Sit down.
- What is it, Howard?

474
00:55:51,500 --> 00:55:57,000
Last night, at 6:00, Winnie took it
in her head to go out looking for me.

475
00:55:57,400 --> 00:56:02,200
I was at Stony's place, while my little
girl was looking for me in some alley.

476
00:56:02,600 --> 00:56:04,500
What happened?

477
00:56:06,900 --> 00:56:10,000
She saw Petis Mulgrew
kill Leroy Wade.

478
00:56:13,200 --> 00:56:15,100
There it is.

479
00:56:16,800 --> 00:56:21,000
Kill him...
That's what we ought to do.

480
00:56:22,100 --> 00:56:25,500
That's what you said too, Socrates?
Isn't that right?

481
00:56:25,900 --> 00:56:30,200
Let's go and shoot him in his head.
- We can't do that, man.

482
00:56:30,700 --> 00:56:34,000
We are not sure whether he did it.
It is just hearsay.

483
00:56:34,300 --> 00:56:39,000
My baby girl is not lying. She saw
Petis jump on Leroy with that knife.

484
00:56:39,400 --> 00:56:42,600
She told that to Corina before
they even found him.

485
00:56:43,000 --> 00:56:46,600
She saw Leroy get it and she saw
who did it.

486
00:56:46,900 --> 00:56:48,300
She could be wrong.

487
00:56:48,600 --> 00:56:53,800
What is wrong with you?
- Nothing, that flu will not go away.

488
00:56:55,200 --> 00:56:59,700
Even if she did see it,
we should still go to the cops.

489
00:57:00,100 --> 00:57:04,500
Will Corina let me talk to Winnie?
- No, she doesn't want to scare her.

490
00:57:04,900 --> 00:57:07,500
Tell me what else did Winnie see?

491
00:57:07,800 --> 00:57:12,900
That crazy fool lives a block away from
my house. Corina is scared to death.

492
00:57:13,300 --> 00:57:16,600
It sounds like a war zone out there.

493
00:57:32,200 --> 00:57:36,600
Listen to that.
Running them down like slaves.

494
00:57:37,000 --> 00:57:39,400
They have got dogs, too.

495
00:57:39,700 --> 00:57:44,900
What do you want us to do, Howard?
- I have to leave soon.

496
00:57:46,000 --> 00:57:52,100
The last two weeks five people have
been mugged here. Petis did it.

497
00:57:52,600 --> 00:57:56,600
Now they are killing people.
- Tell the police.

498
00:57:57,000 --> 00:58:01,000
Dope fiends don't stop until they
are dead. We have to kill them.

499
00:58:01,400 --> 00:58:04,700
We cannot kill him.
- Why not?

500
00:58:05,000 --> 00:58:09,900
Burke, you cannot wash murder off
your hands, you have to live with that.

501
00:58:10,300 --> 00:58:15,600
You should never turn a black man
over to the police, you'd better kill him.

502
00:58:16,300 --> 00:58:18,600
So we cannot do anything.

503
00:58:21,700 --> 00:58:24,000
Will you help us, Socco?

504
00:58:26,500 --> 00:58:30,700
I'll do what I can, but you have
to go to a doctor about that gut.

505
00:58:47,800 --> 00:58:51,400
Remember, let me do the talking.

506
00:59:05,500 --> 00:59:09,000
Who is it?
- Petis, it's me...

507
00:59:10,400 --> 00:59:11,800
Socco.

508
00:59:12,000 --> 00:59:17,000
What do you want?
- We can both earn some money.

509
00:59:27,300 --> 00:59:31,200
We would talk to him.
- That's what I am doing.

510
00:59:31,500 --> 00:59:33,900
This is the only way to get
his attention.

511
00:59:35,600 --> 00:59:38,500
Let me go.
- Girl, put some clothes on.

512
00:59:38,800 --> 00:59:40,600
Are you a friend of my daddy?

513
00:59:41,000 --> 00:59:44,000
Yes. Get your clothes
and get out of here.

514
00:59:49,600 --> 00:59:53,800
What are you going to do with Petis?
- Go on, get out of here.

515
00:59:58,800 --> 01:00:01,700
Look, all right.
She is gone, isn't she?

516
01:00:02,100 --> 01:00:06,200
We know what you did, Petis.
- I didn't do a damn thing.

517
01:00:06,600 --> 01:00:08,800
Get him back on the chair.

518
01:00:14,100 --> 01:00:18,600
Look, let me tell you something...
- Don't talk!

519
01:00:19,000 --> 01:00:22,500
Shut up. No! Don't talk.
- Get the fuck out of my house.

520
01:00:22,800 --> 01:00:24,800
Shut up!

521
01:00:25,100 --> 01:00:29,500
Nobody wants to hear what you
have to say. You have to listen.

522
01:00:30,700 --> 01:00:35,500
We have held a trial.
One man wants to kill you.

523
01:00:36,000 --> 01:00:39,400
Somebody else wants to turn you
over to the police.

524
01:00:39,700 --> 01:00:43,600
We have talked about it
and we have come to a decision.

525
01:00:44,000 --> 01:00:47,300
You have to leave, boy.
- But I haven't done anything.

526
01:00:47,600 --> 01:00:52,300
You have to leave this neighbourhood.

527
01:00:52,700 --> 01:00:55,300
And if you don't go,
then you will die.

528
01:00:56,400 --> 01:01:00,500
I don't know what the hell
you are talking about.

529
01:01:00,900 --> 01:01:06,000
You are out of here at six o'clock.
- Already at six?

530
01:01:08,000 --> 01:01:09,900
Can you repeat that?

531
01:01:12,700 --> 01:01:15,400
I have to say goodbye to my mother.

532
01:01:17,100 --> 01:01:21,500
If you are not gone by six o'clock,
your mama can say goodbye to you.

533
01:01:23,300 --> 01:01:24,800
Come on.

534
01:01:26,600 --> 01:01:28,300
Let's go.

535
01:02:08,100 --> 01:02:10,100
What shall we do?

536
01:02:11,000 --> 01:02:14,100
It's time for you all to go home.

537
01:02:16,900 --> 01:02:21,700
I thought we were in it together.
- Yes. But it's time for you all to go.

538
01:02:24,500 --> 01:02:29,800
What are you going to do, Socco?
- I will hang around here until about six.

539
01:02:37,000 --> 01:02:40,200
We shall go to the clinic
after this, right?

540
01:05:39,200 --> 01:05:44,600
Sure, Socrates heard the boy gasping
and snorting in that dumpster.

541
01:05:45,000 --> 01:05:50,900
But it wasn't worth the mark against
his soul to see that crack head bleed.

542
01:06:37,100 --> 01:06:39,100
Good morning, Mr Fortlow.

543
01:06:43,100 --> 01:06:47,800
I thought you might get hungry.

544
01:06:48,700 --> 01:06:52,300
How is Winnie?
- She is real good.

545
01:06:54,400 --> 01:06:57,400
I wanted to thank you for helping.

546
01:07:08,900 --> 01:07:11,300
I wanted to thank you again.

547
01:07:18,000 --> 01:07:20,200
Is Howard still home?

548
01:07:21,500 --> 01:07:23,300
He's in the house.

549
01:07:24,200 --> 01:07:27,600
He still hasn't got a job,
and he is mad, too.

550
01:07:29,900 --> 01:07:32,400
He told me not to come over here.

551
01:07:32,700 --> 01:07:37,300
But I told him I owed you at least
a breakfast, and a thank you.

552
01:07:38,100 --> 01:07:40,700
Howard is just ashamed.

553
01:07:41,800 --> 01:07:46,400
He thinks he is no man any more.
But he will come around it though.

554
01:07:48,400 --> 01:07:50,300
Besides, he knows...

555
01:07:51,600 --> 01:07:55,200
that there are men enough
that will carry your load, woman.

556
01:07:56,400 --> 01:07:58,400
Whole lot of men.

557
01:08:02,800 --> 01:08:09,100
That touch meant a lot to him.
She knew things he would never know.

558
01:08:09,600 --> 01:08:13,000
When she woke up,
she thought about a better life.

559
01:08:13,300 --> 01:08:18,300
And maybe with that touch, could
Socrates see something better, too.

560
01:08:26,800 --> 01:08:29,400
Hey, you. I want you.

561
01:08:30,100 --> 01:08:31,900
Get him.

562
01:08:33,900 --> 01:08:36,700
Did you turn on me, nigger?
- No.

563
01:08:37,000 --> 01:08:42,900
Yes, you did. You told the police
where to find the body.

564
01:08:43,400 --> 01:08:45,700
You told the police.
- No, I didn't.

565
01:08:47,900 --> 01:08:51,500
I do not hope to see
your sorry ass any more, sissy.

566
01:08:52,000 --> 01:08:55,400
That's okay. Let him run.

567
01:08:55,800 --> 01:08:58,400
I know where the motherfucker lives.

568
01:09:57,100 --> 01:10:00,300
Socrates had some hard fights
in his life.

569
01:10:00,600 --> 01:10:03,900
But the hardest was
when he couldn't do anything.

570
01:10:30,400 --> 01:10:32,900
He never liked talking to doctors...

571
01:10:33,200 --> 01:10:37,600
because he said they never answered
a question except to tell him lies.

572
01:10:38,600 --> 01:10:41,500
He wondered what lies
they were going to tell him now.

573
01:10:57,300 --> 01:10:59,600
Did you ever fix any furniture before?

574
01:11:00,100 --> 01:11:03,500
I could get some glue down in here...

575
01:11:03,900 --> 01:11:07,700
brace it, and hold it together
with a belt...

576
01:11:08,000 --> 01:11:10,800
then these legs are stronger
than they were before.

577
01:11:14,300 --> 01:11:18,700
Some of the things they teach
you in prison are useful.

578
01:11:19,300 --> 01:11:23,800
But it's only useful if they don't
cut you down in the streets first.

579
01:11:29,000 --> 01:11:31,900
Socrates saw that Darryl
was scared.

580
01:11:32,200 --> 01:11:36,100
Scared what he had to do
to be a man.

581
01:11:36,500 --> 01:11:40,500
Are your foster parents not mad
at you, for not coming home?

582
01:11:42,800 --> 01:11:46,600
Once I was gone for four days.
They never knew.

583
01:11:46,900 --> 01:11:49,500
Help me turn over the table.

584
01:11:49,800 --> 01:11:52,800
Ready. Easy.

585
01:11:53,200 --> 01:11:56,300
Man, there is no easy thing
in South Central.

586
01:11:56,600 --> 01:12:00,100
Down here you don't have
to join the army to go to war.

587
01:12:03,000 --> 01:12:07,500
Do you remember our discussion?
- About Phillip and them?

588
01:12:11,400 --> 01:12:15,000
Put that down easy, Darryl.

589
01:12:16,500 --> 01:12:18,600
All right. Today is the day.

590
01:12:20,400 --> 01:12:22,500
Are you scared?

591
01:12:32,400 --> 01:12:34,500
Are they the ones?

592
01:12:53,400 --> 01:12:55,800
Don't you move, man.

593
01:12:58,400 --> 01:13:01,400
I would better look out for
your friend there, Socrates.

594
01:13:04,500 --> 01:13:08,300
I told you to keep your ugly face away.
- You don't scare me.

595
01:13:08,600 --> 01:13:10,600
You'd better go and help him.

596
01:13:10,900 --> 01:13:13,900
Don't talk to me, you little fuck.

597
01:13:20,800 --> 01:13:25,100
Come on, show me what you've got.
I will kick your ass.

598
01:13:26,700 --> 01:13:30,300
Your boy is in big trouble over there,
Mr Fortlow.

599
01:13:33,600 --> 01:13:36,100
Come on, you little punk.

600
01:13:41,100 --> 01:13:43,200
Turn over.

601
01:13:47,800 --> 01:13:50,300
I'm going to kick your ass,
you piece of shit.

602
01:13:57,100 --> 01:14:00,600
Do you hear me? Do you see me?
- Who are you?

603
01:14:01,000 --> 01:14:03,300
Watch out, Socco.

604
01:14:24,700 --> 01:14:26,900
Don't look at me.

605
01:14:37,600 --> 01:14:39,600
Hit the deck.

606
01:15:03,800 --> 01:15:05,900
I was scared.

607
01:15:06,200 --> 01:15:11,100
You gave him a good punch, boy.
It landed right on his chin.

608
01:15:14,100 --> 01:15:19,000
Come on, Darryl. You stood up for
yourself, that's all you can do.

609
01:15:21,600 --> 01:15:24,800
You are always outnumbered.

610
01:15:25,200 --> 01:15:30,400
They will still come after me.
- Yes, but you stood up.

611
01:15:30,800 --> 01:15:36,600
Now, there's nothing to be
ashamed for the rest of your life.

612
01:15:37,900 --> 01:15:40,000
How is that going to help me?

613
01:15:45,900 --> 01:15:48,400
You have done your job.

614
01:15:48,700 --> 01:15:52,100
Now it's up to me,
to find myself a job.

615
01:15:53,500 --> 01:15:56,200
Maybe I can help you.

616
01:16:06,800 --> 01:16:11,600
I'm afraid it's bad news. I got a fax
saying that they cannot hire you...

617
01:16:12,000 --> 01:16:17,000
because you do not have a phone and
you live too far away from the store.

618
01:16:17,400 --> 01:16:19,400
Can I see it?
- I threw it away.

619
01:16:19,700 --> 01:16:25,000
Please leave, or I will go to the police,
if you don't stop harassing us.

620
01:16:25,400 --> 01:16:27,600
I'm only asking for a job.

621
01:16:27,900 --> 01:16:31,200
The police will arrest you
if you come here again.

622
01:16:52,700 --> 01:16:54,700
What do you want?

623
01:16:55,000 --> 01:16:58,600
You have no business here,
Socrates Fortlow.

624
01:16:59,000 --> 01:17:02,600
We just come here for a visit.

625
01:17:03,000 --> 01:17:07,800
You trick yourself into my house with
a boy. You are not welcome here.

626
01:17:08,200 --> 01:17:11,100
I am his best friend, Luvia.

627
01:17:11,400 --> 01:17:13,700
You cannot deny him that.
Not now.

628
01:17:16,400 --> 01:17:21,000
Do you have a gun on you?
I don't want weapons in my house.

629
01:17:21,400 --> 01:17:23,900
I am unarmed, officer.

630
01:17:38,200 --> 01:17:44,200
I don't want any foolishness in there.
I'll be back in twenty minutes.

631
01:17:44,700 --> 01:17:47,300
Mr Burke needs his sleep.

632
01:17:53,200 --> 01:17:55,400
Take it easy.

633
01:18:03,500 --> 01:18:05,900
How do you feel?

634
01:18:06,200 --> 01:18:09,700
It's like when they told me
it might be cancer.

635
01:18:10,100 --> 01:18:14,100
I had trouble standing up.

636
01:18:15,500 --> 01:18:19,600
And then after a week of tests... shit.

637
01:18:20,600 --> 01:18:22,600
Are you in pain?

638
01:18:27,000 --> 01:18:29,600
Can I borrow your gun, Socco?

639
01:18:30,600 --> 01:18:32,300
For what?

640
01:18:34,400 --> 01:18:36,300
You know.

641
01:18:37,900 --> 01:18:42,500
The doctors say,
I might have got three, six months.

642
01:18:43,600 --> 01:18:48,700
They said that they cannot give me
a good pain killer...

643
01:18:49,100 --> 01:18:53,100
until they have tried
chemo or radiation.

644
01:18:53,500 --> 01:18:56,100
And now they are telling me...

645
01:18:57,200 --> 01:19:02,200
that they cannot treat me right,
because I am not insured properly.

646
01:19:03,700 --> 01:19:05,800
Do you want to shoot yourself?

647
01:19:13,200 --> 01:19:17,600
I cannot do that.
- I can pay you for it.

648
01:19:18,000 --> 01:19:22,700
I have put away part of my
social security since I live here.

649
01:19:23,100 --> 01:19:27,900
Luvia will call the cops
as soon as I bring a gun.

650
01:19:28,300 --> 01:19:32,700
Let us meet on the street.
- How will you do that? You are ill.

651
01:19:33,100 --> 01:19:37,900
Luvia says that you do not eat.
- That is because of the pain.

652
01:19:39,600 --> 01:19:44,700
I cannot walk or eat
because it hurts so much.

653
01:19:54,100 --> 01:19:57,000
Go downstairs and wait for me.

654
01:20:10,400 --> 01:20:12,500
Your twenty minutes are up.

655
01:20:13,500 --> 01:20:17,000
We need to talk for a few more
minutes. I'll be right down.

656
01:20:17,400 --> 01:20:21,400
I need to speak with him for a few
more minutes. Excuse us.

657
01:20:32,300 --> 01:20:36,500
How much money do you have?
- Over seventeen hundred dollars.

658
01:20:36,900 --> 01:20:40,000
I saved it over the last five years.

659
01:20:40,300 --> 01:20:43,900
It's in the bottom
of the bottom drawer of the bureau.

660
01:20:54,100 --> 01:20:57,400
I was saving it for Luvia.

661
01:20:57,700 --> 01:21:01,500
But I want you to take it
and get me a piece.

662
01:21:03,900 --> 01:21:07,300
After I am gone,
you can give the rest to her.

663
01:21:15,900 --> 01:21:20,200
I will take two hundred dollars.
If I have to, I will get you a gun.

664
01:21:21,300 --> 01:21:27,600
But I am going to try
and help you first.

665
01:21:28,100 --> 01:21:32,700
Don't give up because
you cannot pay the doctors.

666
01:21:36,500 --> 01:21:38,600
Doctors are not everything.

667
01:22:42,000 --> 01:22:46,400
I heard that I had to talk to you.
- Who told you that? Reba?

668
01:22:46,900 --> 01:22:50,200
Did the woman behind the bar
tell you to come up here?

669
01:22:51,500 --> 01:22:56,400
Because if she did, you had better
take your ass and get out of here.

670
01:22:59,200 --> 01:23:01,600
I will leave.

671
01:23:02,000 --> 01:23:04,600
When I get what I came for.

672
01:23:07,200 --> 01:23:09,800
Are you trying to fuck with me?

673
01:23:10,100 --> 01:23:13,200
You will feel it
when I fuck with you, brother.

674
01:23:16,300 --> 01:23:19,600
I burst you open
like a goddamned watermelon.

675
01:23:22,100 --> 01:23:24,000
What do you want then?

676
01:23:58,000 --> 01:24:00,400
Have you heard from the hospital?

677
01:24:03,100 --> 01:24:07,200
They said it is definitely cancer.

678
01:24:18,500 --> 01:24:24,400
You are not calling long distance here.
- I got the local number right here.

679
01:24:36,600 --> 01:24:40,700
Valley Enterprises.
Can I help you?

680
01:24:41,100 --> 01:24:45,800
It is about my application for a job
at your store on Beverly Glen.

681
01:24:46,300 --> 01:24:52,600
How do you spell the last name?
- F-o-r-t-l-o-w, Fortlow.

682
01:24:54,800 --> 01:24:57,600
There is no record of your application.

683
01:24:58,000 --> 01:25:02,500
But Miss Grimes said that you faxed
that you couldn't hire me...

684
01:25:02,900 --> 01:25:06,400
because I have no phone
and I live too far from there.

685
01:25:06,700 --> 01:25:10,500
Those are not our requirements. And
there is no record of your application.

686
01:25:10,900 --> 01:25:14,000
Maybe you threw it away
when you rejected it?

687
01:25:14,300 --> 01:25:18,600
Every application is put
on the computer, so it must be here.

688
01:25:19,000 --> 01:25:22,800
Thank you very much, madam.

689
01:26:02,000 --> 01:26:05,200
My name is Parker
and this is Mr Weems.

690
01:26:05,500 --> 01:26:07,800
We work for
Kingman Security Services.

691
01:26:08,100 --> 01:26:10,700
Would you like to come upstairs?

692
01:26:11,700 --> 01:26:14,000
No.
- Just to talk.

693
01:26:17,000 --> 01:26:19,100
Have a seat, Mr Fortlow.

694
01:26:21,200 --> 01:26:23,000
Coffee?

695
01:26:26,300 --> 01:26:27,600
What is it?

696
01:26:27,800 --> 01:26:30,100
What do you have
against Miss Grimes?

697
01:26:30,400 --> 01:26:34,100
I need a job.
- She said you are harassing her.

698
01:26:34,500 --> 01:26:39,200
You need a phone number for a job.
- That's bullshit.

699
01:26:39,600 --> 01:26:44,000
Do I have to starve because
I cannot afford a phone?

700
01:26:48,300 --> 01:26:53,000
I need a job.
- But you intimidate people.

701
01:26:53,400 --> 01:26:57,000
What am I supposed to do?
- You cannot work here.

702
01:26:57,300 --> 01:27:01,200
They are scared that you would
come in here with your gun blazing.

703
01:27:03,500 --> 01:27:07,300
What kind of game are you playing?
- What do you mean?

704
01:27:07,600 --> 01:27:12,600
Do you really want a job?
- Yes, that's why I am here.

705
01:27:13,500 --> 01:27:17,800
I cannot sit on my ass because
somebody does not like my skin.

706
01:27:26,800 --> 01:27:30,000
You can work for a market
about five blocks away.

707
01:27:30,400 --> 01:27:35,800
The manager is Gonzalez.
You will not scare Bobby Gonzalez.

708
01:27:36,200 --> 01:27:41,200
Maybe we can talk to him about you.
But I have just one more question.

709
01:27:50,500 --> 01:27:52,500
I got the job.

710
01:27:53,400 --> 01:27:55,500
At the supermarket?

711
01:27:57,200 --> 01:27:59,100
What did you say?

712
01:28:00,300 --> 01:28:04,100
About what?
- On your application.

713
01:28:06,400 --> 01:28:11,200
When they asked
about your prison record.

714
01:28:13,000 --> 01:28:19,700
There were two security guards,
Parker and Weems. Ex-LAPD.

715
01:28:20,200 --> 01:28:23,600
They knew that I was an ex-con
right off the bat.

716
01:28:25,800 --> 01:28:27,600
So what did you say?

717
01:28:27,900 --> 01:28:31,800
I told them that they didn't have
to look into that.

718
01:28:32,300 --> 01:28:34,600
And when they check it later?

719
01:28:35,600 --> 01:28:40,100
I will work until they fire me and
then I will get another job. Or not.

720
01:28:46,700 --> 01:28:50,100
What do you want to eat?
- I was about to ask you.

721
01:28:51,500 --> 01:28:53,600
What then?

722
01:28:53,900 --> 01:28:56,300
Do you want to have dinner with me?

723
01:28:58,000 --> 01:29:00,400
I don't believe it.

724
01:29:00,700 --> 01:29:03,900
All this time you have
never asked me out to dinner.

725
01:29:04,400 --> 01:29:07,300
I never had a job before.
I had nothing to offer.

726
01:29:07,600 --> 01:29:11,900
A man cannot be with a woman
if he cannot pay the bills.

727
01:29:20,400 --> 01:29:22,800
Do you want to go or not?

728
01:29:25,300 --> 01:29:28,100
Put those in the box.

729
01:29:33,100 --> 01:29:35,300
Mom, the door.

730
01:29:43,000 --> 01:29:48,000
This is my friend, Darryl.
Darryl, this is Corina.

731
01:29:48,400 --> 01:29:51,900
We brought you something.

732
01:29:53,300 --> 01:29:55,900
Mr Fortlow has got something for us.

733
01:29:59,200 --> 01:30:01,300
I didn't know that you are moving.

734
01:30:02,900 --> 01:30:07,400
Howard got a nighttime
computer operator's job in Venice.

735
01:30:07,900 --> 01:30:11,600
We got a place over there.
- That's good, Howard.

736
01:30:12,000 --> 01:30:14,100
That's real good, Howard.

737
01:30:17,600 --> 01:30:21,100
I guess, that will make this
your going away present.

738
01:30:30,800 --> 01:30:34,500
I don't get it.
What is this for?

739
01:30:34,900 --> 01:30:40,600
I found this table, Howard. It was
all broken down and scarred up.

740
01:30:42,100 --> 01:30:48,900
I put it back together.
I glued, sanded and sealed it.

741
01:30:52,700 --> 01:30:56,800
And now I give it to you. Because
every time you sit down to eat at it...

742
01:30:57,100 --> 01:31:01,700
I want you to say thank you
for everything.

743
01:31:05,600 --> 01:31:08,600
I don't know what to say.

744
01:31:11,800 --> 01:31:15,200
I just wish there was something
we could do for you.

745
01:31:21,500 --> 01:31:24,600
There is something
that you could do for me.

746
01:31:32,900 --> 01:31:35,500
Come on, Darryl.
- Give us a minute, Howard.

747
01:31:35,800 --> 01:31:37,800
Hurry up.

748
01:31:39,400 --> 01:31:41,600
Do you have everything?

749
01:31:41,900 --> 01:31:44,000
Why do I have to go with them?

750
01:31:44,300 --> 01:31:49,000
It isn't safe around here
with Phillip and the others.

751
01:31:50,700 --> 01:31:54,900
In Venice you get a chance
for a new start at a new school.

752
01:31:55,300 --> 01:31:57,600
I like being here.

753
01:31:57,900 --> 01:32:01,300
I cannot get custody of you, Darryl.

754
01:32:01,700 --> 01:32:04,600
Howard and Corina
already got a family.

755
01:32:04,800 --> 01:32:08,500
Social Services will pay them
money for you to stay with them.

756
01:32:11,900 --> 01:32:16,300
Are you scared of going to a new place?
- A little.

757
01:32:17,500 --> 01:32:19,400
That's good.

758
01:32:20,700 --> 01:32:25,200
They have gangs in Venice.
So you have to watch out.

759
01:32:28,200 --> 01:32:32,200
Don't get in with any gangs.
- I don't want that, no way.

760
01:32:37,800 --> 01:32:39,800
Are you ready?

761
01:32:46,300 --> 01:32:50,000
Are you going to see Mr Burke?
- Yes, right after this.

762
01:32:50,400 --> 01:32:54,000
Tell him I hope he is feeling better.

763
01:32:59,800 --> 01:33:05,300
You have to sit in the back there,
Darryl. I got a space for you.

764
01:33:10,100 --> 01:33:12,700
I'll see you on Saturday.

765
01:33:13,600 --> 01:33:17,600
Then I will teach Howard to barbecue.
- In your dreams.

766
01:33:19,300 --> 01:33:24,300
Thanks for looking after Darryl.
- We already got him a school.

767
01:33:26,300 --> 01:33:30,800
I will send you 100 dollars each
month. He doesn't eat that much.

768
01:33:31,300 --> 01:33:34,600
Don't worry, Socco,
we will take real good care of him.

769
01:34:08,700 --> 01:34:11,800
I am still a little woozy.
A little bit.

770
01:34:13,600 --> 01:34:19,200
That is because of those drugs.
That's powerful shit.

771
01:34:21,700 --> 01:34:25,700
How many are you taking?
- Until the pain stops.

772
01:34:26,100 --> 01:34:29,700
Three, four, every four hours.

773
01:34:30,600 --> 01:34:34,400
Are you drinking?
- Just a drop of wine or two.

774
01:34:34,900 --> 01:34:38,100
And a shot of Scotch
before I go to sleep.

775
01:34:38,500 --> 01:34:43,500
Don't drink too much.
Alcohol and morphine do not mix.

776
01:34:47,600 --> 01:34:50,500
Do you want to go out tonight?
- Where?

777
01:34:50,900 --> 01:34:56,400
Dilly's Bar.
- A sick man has no business there.

778
01:34:56,800 --> 01:34:59,800
I want to drink in a bar.

779
01:35:00,100 --> 01:35:04,400
I want to look at some long legs
on a woman.

780
01:35:16,200 --> 01:35:20,600
This whiskey makes me see double,
Socco.

781
01:35:21,100 --> 01:35:24,800
And one of you is plenty ugly as it is.

782
01:35:35,500 --> 01:35:38,800
Do you know why I like you, Socco?

783
01:35:39,200 --> 01:35:43,500
Because you do not know any better.
That's why.

784
01:35:45,100 --> 01:35:48,300
Ouvrez la porte.
- What do you say?

785
01:35:50,300 --> 01:35:54,700
Ouvrez la porte.
That's what we used to say in Paris.

786
01:35:55,100 --> 01:35:58,800
Open up...
because Uncle Sam is here.

787
01:35:59,200 --> 01:36:01,000
Those were the days, man.

788
01:36:01,300 --> 01:36:04,500
A gun in my hand,
a sweet girl on my left.

789
01:36:04,900 --> 01:36:08,100
I could have died then.
I should have died.

790
01:36:08,400 --> 01:36:11,200
No man, then we would
have missed you.

791
01:36:11,500 --> 01:36:16,300
I would have missed you. All through
the war, I never met one like you.

792
01:36:16,800 --> 01:36:19,200
What is exactly 'one like me'?

793
01:36:21,000 --> 01:36:22,900
A hero.

794
01:36:24,800 --> 01:36:28,400
You are the closest thing to a hero
I have ever met.

795
01:36:28,700 --> 01:36:30,700
You must be drunk.

796
01:36:33,300 --> 01:36:35,300
Sweet Charla.

797
01:36:37,900 --> 01:36:44,100
Here it is. Fifty dollars
for all the Scotch you bring.

798
01:36:44,600 --> 01:36:47,700
Thanks.
Is it your birthday?

799
01:36:48,000 --> 01:36:53,800
No, Charla.
I'm going back to my family.

800
01:36:54,300 --> 01:36:57,100
Where is home?
- Down south.

801
01:36:57,300 --> 01:37:01,400
When are you leaving?
- Later tonight.

802
01:37:05,400 --> 01:37:07,500
What are you talking about?

803
01:37:39,600 --> 01:37:43,400
You are a real hero.
Not many left like you.

804
01:37:43,800 --> 01:37:46,300
Not many so stupid as me.

805
01:37:46,600 --> 01:37:50,600
You are no fool, Socrates Fortlow.

806
01:37:51,100 --> 01:37:55,800
I never said anything
that you didn't already knew.

807
01:37:56,200 --> 01:37:58,500
Because you are a thinking man.

808
01:37:58,800 --> 01:38:02,400
I never had any knowledge
that you didn't knew.

809
01:38:02,800 --> 01:38:05,700
At least, up to now.

810
01:38:06,400 --> 01:38:08,500
What do you know now?

811
01:38:08,800 --> 01:38:12,900
About death.
I can tell you all about death.

812
01:38:14,100 --> 01:38:16,000
Cold and clear.

813
01:38:19,000 --> 01:38:22,900
Are you scared, Burke?
- I am scared of the pain.

814
01:38:23,300 --> 01:38:27,600
But I am not scared of death.
Not now.

815
01:38:29,600 --> 01:38:31,000
Is it the dope?
- No.

816
01:38:31,200 --> 01:38:34,500
Even before you got me my drug,
I could feel it.

817
01:38:35,000 --> 01:38:41,000
I laid in my room late at night
with an ice pack on my belly.

818
01:38:41,400 --> 01:38:45,400
If I laid still enough,
I could feel it.

819
01:38:45,800 --> 01:38:49,100
Like icy silver snakes
were moving up and down my body.

820
01:38:49,500 --> 01:38:52,400
Sliding and singing.

821
01:38:52,700 --> 01:38:55,500
If I was real quiet...

822
01:38:57,500 --> 01:39:02,100
that feeling would take over
and I would be on the other side.

823
01:39:04,400 --> 01:39:09,000
While I am dying,
something else is coming to life.

824
01:39:22,600 --> 01:39:25,400
I was scared to die.

825
01:39:25,700 --> 01:39:27,900
Now I am ready to let go.

826
01:39:30,800 --> 01:39:34,600
I had a couple of things
that I needed to do first.

827
01:39:35,000 --> 01:39:38,400
What do you want?
- I wanted to have a drink...

828
01:39:38,800 --> 01:39:44,200
a flirt with a pretty girl
and a talk with my best friend.

829
01:39:55,200 --> 01:39:57,000
There you go.

830
01:40:04,400 --> 01:40:08,200
Do you want to go home?
- That's what I told Charla.

831
01:40:09,900 --> 01:40:13,500
What do you think about me, Socrates?
- You mean?

832
01:40:13,900 --> 01:40:17,100
I want to know what you see
when you look at me.

833
01:40:17,400 --> 01:40:18,900
I always wanted to know...

834
01:40:19,200 --> 01:40:23,700
but that's not a question
one man should ask another.

835
01:40:24,000 --> 01:40:25,600
What are you saying now?

836
01:40:25,900 --> 01:40:28,900
Tell me what you see
when you look at me.

837
01:40:33,200 --> 01:40:35,100
I don't know.

838
01:40:36,300 --> 01:40:39,100
I don't know.
What do you want me to say?

839
01:40:41,000 --> 01:40:43,000
You are my friend.

840
01:40:46,300 --> 01:40:48,200
A real friend.

841
01:41:08,400 --> 01:41:12,400
I will get a taxi.
You wait right here.

842
01:41:12,800 --> 01:41:18,400
No, let's wait for a bus.
I like to watch the lights.

843
01:41:24,600 --> 01:41:26,800
I know what you see.

844
01:41:28,400 --> 01:41:30,500
I know what you see.

845
01:41:32,400 --> 01:41:37,200
I know you love me, man.
I love you, too.

846
01:41:50,000 --> 01:41:53,900
Help me to get my pills
out of my pocket, will you?

847
01:41:59,800 --> 01:42:04,800
Pour me out ten.
No, twelve and then take it away.

848
01:42:05,200 --> 01:42:08,300
You don't need to take any more
of these now.

849
01:42:09,800 --> 01:42:13,000
You need to wait until the morning.

850
01:42:24,900 --> 01:42:26,900
The bus is coming.

851
01:42:28,200 --> 01:42:32,500
Leave me here, man.
Get on the bus and go home.

852
01:42:32,800 --> 01:42:37,400
I am not leaving you out here.
- You cannot save me.

853
01:42:37,800 --> 01:42:41,700
Not this time.
- You are my friend.

854
01:42:42,000 --> 01:42:45,000
The doctor said I'm dead, man.

855
01:42:46,600 --> 01:42:52,200
Dead. Tonight is the best night
that I will never have again.

856
01:42:57,000 --> 01:42:59,600
And you did that for me.

857
01:43:02,200 --> 01:43:05,000
Your job is done, Socrates.

858
01:43:07,600 --> 01:43:10,200
Now it is time to die.

859
01:43:11,100 --> 01:43:13,300
Hey, it's all right.

860
01:43:20,900 --> 01:43:22,900
Go on, now.

861
01:43:36,000 --> 01:43:38,200
Come on.

862
01:43:45,400 --> 01:43:47,300
What's wrong with you?

863
01:43:49,400 --> 01:43:51,500
Get on or get off.

864
01:44:27,900 --> 01:44:31,600
I couldn't see him,
but I knew that he was there.

865
01:44:32,100 --> 01:44:35,800
He was looking after me,
even in death.

866
01:44:37,100 --> 01:44:41,800
That bus was carrying him to places
most men couldn't even imagine.

867
01:44:42,200 --> 01:44:46,000
And Socrates had been as low
as a man could go.

868
01:44:46,400 --> 01:44:51,500
But he came back loving hard
and deep and strong.

869
01:44:51,900 --> 01:44:55,300
A rich man would never have
that kind of power.

870
01:44:55,800 --> 01:45:00,300
And precious few lovers
could ever be that satisfied.

871
01:48:06,000 --> 01:48:11,000
Turkish